# Code Style and Formatting Standards

## Overview

These guidelines ensure consistency across our codebase, covering TypeScript/JavaScript, Markdown, and general formatting standards.

## TypeScript/JavaScript Standards

### File Organization

- One component per file
- Clear file naming (PascalCase for components)
- Logical grouping of related files
- Consistent directory structure

### Code Structure

- Function declarations using `function` keyword
- Consistent use of arrow functions for callbacks
- Clear separation of concerns
- Logical grouping of methods

### Naming Conventions

- PascalCase for components and types
- camelCase for variables and functions
- UPPER_CASE for constants
- Descriptive and meaningful names
- Prefix boolean variables with is/has/should

### Component Structure

```typescript
// Imports
import { type FC } from 'react';
import { useQuery } from '@tanstack/react-query';

// Types
interface Props {
  id: string;
  name: string;
}

// Component
export const MyComponent: FC<Props> = ({ id, name }) => {
  // Hooks
  const query = useQuery({ ... });

  // Handlers
  const handleClick = () => {
    // ...
  };

  // Render
  return (
    <div>
      {/* JSX */}
    </div>
  );
};
```

## Prettier Configuration

### Base Configuration

```javascript
// .prettierrc.js
module.exports = {
  semi: true,
  trailingComma: 'all',
  singleQuote: true,
  printWidth: 80,
  tabWidth: 2,
  useTabs: false,
  bracketSpacing: true,
  jsxBracketSameLine: false,
  arrowParens: 'always',
  endOfLine: 'lf',
};
```

### File-Specific Overrides

```javascript
// .prettierrc.js overrides
module.exports = {
  overrides: [
    {
      files: '*.{md,mdc}',
      options: {
        parser: 'markdown',
        proseWrap: 'always',
        printWidth: 80,
        tabWidth: 2,
        endOfLine: 'lf',
      },
    },
    {
      files: '*.{ts,tsx}',
      options: {
        parser: 'typescript',
        semi: true,
        trailingComma: 'all',
        endOfLine: 'lf',
      },
    },
  ],
};
```

## Markdown Standards

### File Structure

```markdown
---
description: 'Clear description of the file contents'
globs: 'pattern'
---

# Title (H1)

## Section (H2)

### Subsection (H3)

Content with proper spacing.
```

### Markdown Rules

- Use ATX-style headers (`#` for h1, `##` for h2)
- Maximum line length of 80 characters (except code blocks)
- Use dashes (`-`) for unordered lists
- Use backticks for inline code
- Use fenced code blocks with language specification
- One blank line before and after headings
- No multiple consecutive blank lines
- Use reference-style links for better readability
- Include alt text for images
- End files with a single newline

### Documentation Best Practices

- Clear and concise descriptions
- Proper section hierarchy
- Consistent formatting
- Meaningful examples
- Proper cross-referencing

## Best Practices

### General

- Keep functions small and focused
- Use early returns
- Avoid nested conditionals
- Use guard clauses
- Prefer immutability

### TypeScript

- Use strict type checking
- Avoid `any` type
- Use interface for objects
- Use type for unions/intersections
- Document complex types

### React

- Use functional components
- Follow hooks rules
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Use proper prop types
- Implement proper cleanup

### Testing

- Clear test descriptions
- One assertion per test
- Proper test isolation
- Consistent testing patterns
- Meaningful test coverage

